section.subtitle: AirCover is comprehensive protection included for free with every booking.

features.title: Booking Protection Guarantee
features.subtitle: In the unlikely event that a Host needs to cancel your booking within 30 days of check-in, we’ll find you a similar or better home or we’ll refund you.

features.title: Check-In Guarantee
features.subtitle: If you can’t check into your home and the Host cannot resolve the issue, we’ll find you a similar or better home for the length of your original stay or we’ll refund you.

features.title: Get-What-You-Booked Guarantee
features.subtitle: If at any time during your stay you find your listing isn't as advertised – for example, the refrigerator stops working and your Host can’t easily fix it, or it has fewer bedrooms than listed – you'll have three days to report it and we’ll find you a similar or better home, or we’ll refund you.

features.title: 24-hour Safety Line
features.subtitle: If you ever feel unsafe, you’ll get priority access to specially trained safety agents, day or night.

section.title: Things to know
section.additionalHouseRules:
Children under 12 must be supervised at all times by an adult who will take responsibility for their safety
- We do not recommend the cabins for children under 5 due to a steep ladder and woodburning stove 
- Whilst the cabins are private we do request that noise is kept to a minimum after 10 pm as there may be other guests on site
- Check in from 3.30 pm - 6.30 p.m.- check out 10 am
- We supply a base sheet for the double mattress and sofa bed and there is a double duvet and 4 pillows in the house - YOU WILL NEED TO BRING A DUVET COVER, PILLOW CASES AND TOWELS - unless arranged with owner
- The person who's name is on the booking will be held responsible for all guests and will ensure they adhere to the house rules
- You accept that the responsibility for personal property of guests occupying the accommodation is solely theirs. All vehicles are also left at the guest’s risk. Guests agree to absolve the Owner of any responsibility for any accident or mishap to persons or property whilst on the premises or whilst engaged in any activity therein, or from any illness or injury arising from any causes whatsoever.
- You agree to use the Property solely for its intended purpose as self-catering accommodation and to accept the Owners right to refuse to hand over the Property to any person deemed unsuitable to take charge. Causing a nuisance or disturbance to neighbours or other guests, unreasonable behaviour or disrupting the running of the farm may result in the Owner requesting you to leave.
- You agree to allow the Owners or agents access to the Property at all reasonable times. We will only ever request access to your property in case of an emergency, e.g. a water leak.
- You must respect and look after your accommodation during your stay and you must leave the Property clean and tidy. Please let us know of any damage or breakages so we can repair or replace them for the next guests. We reserve the right to charge for any damage or breakages.

htmlDescription.htmlText:
A stunning, hand crafted cabin with your own private wood fired hot tub and wood burning oven located in the beautiful North Cotswold Countryside. A haven to escape to for couples and families from all walks of life.

To truly relax you do not need to drive anywhere as we are just a 5 minute walk from the pretty village of Mickleton where there are 2 pubs, a village shop, post office, butchers and hotel.

IF BOOKED CHECK OUR OTHER CABINS - DAISY'S DEN, DJ'S DIGS, MIRTS MANSION AND JEDS SHED

The space
The houses have been built to our own specifications and alongside the hot tub and cooker they contain a micro kitchen, 2 ring hob, fridge and ice box. There is also a flush toilet and outside hot water Shower Shack at the rear of your cabin.

Guest access
Located at the end of our small touring campsite the cabins have their own large fenced areas to provide privacy for guests

Other things to note
The hot tubs are wood fired and can take up to 4 hours to heat - they are all emptied, cleaned and refilled for you on the day of your arrival so are normally ready for lighting around 3pm so will be hot on your first evening here - we explain how to manage the hot tub on your arrival. Please note there are no jets as it uses fresh water and no chemicals.
